@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/v1
@accessToken = paste-access-token-here

### Create expense
# @name createExpense
POST {{baseUrl}}/expenses
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Groceries",
  "amount": 42.5,
  "currency": "USD",
  "category": "food",
  "date": "2026-07-12T00:00:00.000Z",
  "notes": "Weekly shop"
}

### List expenses (pagination + filtering + sorting)
# Query params: page, limit (pagination, default 1/10)
#               category, currency, search (exact/exact/partial-title match)
#               minAmount, maxAmount (inclusive amount range)
#               dateFrom, dateTo (inclusive ISO8601 date range)
#               sortBy (comma-separated "field:order", fields: date|amount|title, order: asc|desc)
GET {{baseUrl}}/expenses?page=1&limit=10&category=food&currency=USD&search=grocer&minAmount=0&maxAmount=1000&dateFrom=2026-01-01T00:00:00.000Z&dateTo=2026-12-31T23:59:59.000Z&sortBy=date:desc,amount:asc
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Get expense by id (uses id from the create response above)
GET {{baseUrl}}/expenses/{{createExpense.response.body.$.data.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Update expense (uses id from the create response above)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/expenses/{{createExpense.response.body.$.data.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 50
}

### Delete expense (uses id from the create response above)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/expenses/{{createExpense.response.body.$.data.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
